<TITLE> India army says Pakistan deployed troops on border </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan has deployed troops along the border with India since the Mumbai attacks but India was not being provoked, the Indian army chief said on Wednesday. "The aspect of some (Pakistani) troops coming towards the east ... we are aware. That has happened," General Deepak Kapoor told reporters. They have come to the eastern border of Pakistan with India." But he said India was not provoked and New Delhi would not indulge in any war hysteria.
